summary: I think one of my favorite things about Captain Marvel is how, once Carol realized/unleashed her full power - SHE HAD FUN WITH...
body:
I think one of my favorite things about Captain Marvel is how, once Carol realized/unleashed her full power - SHE HAD FUN WITH IT! Literally screaming “Wooo hoo!” and shit. Man, after a lifetime of “oh no woo is me. My super human abilities are such a burden. I don’t want them. I am cursed *sulk* *sulk* *sulk* *brood* *brood*”*

Like the good guys always have some shame attached to their powers and the bad guys are like stoked on theirs. Over it.

I’m happy Carol realizes she’s the shit and the most powerful thing on and around earth and feels no need to be humble about it.

[*I’m talking about TV shows mostly. Not these Marvel movies]

summary: Henlo uhm I'm here to request some short soulmate stuff with either Nat or Carol I'm sksks soft
question: Henlo uhm I'm here to request some short soulmate stuff with either Nat or Carol I'm sksks soft
answer:
decided on the: first you find your platonic soulmate and then /they/ find your romantic soulmate!au (also I was gonna post this on my sfw but i got tired)

  • you met Carol at the fair one summer while you were visiting family when you were both teens
  • she was arguing with one of the (totally not rigged) game booths that you knew how to beat so you walked up and decided to help a cute girl out
  • it wasn’t until you passed her the biggest (and ugliest) bear that she hugged you and both of you felt a jolt shudder through both your bodies - the sign of your platonic soulmate
  • “guess we’re stuck together - you, me, and that ugly bear I won for you.” you smiled and couldn’t help but laugh when her and random people around you looked at you with wide eyes
  • you met maria during your college days and introduced her to Carol when you found out they both wanted to be pilots + imagine your surprise (you weren’t) when they found out they were romantic soulmates!!!
  • Carol felt bad that you always helped her out and found her romantic soulmate when she never got the feeling for yours
  • that is
  • until she met the Black Widow
  • after coming back to earth and helping the Avengers, something about Natasha didn’t sit quite right with her, and after making sure her wife and daughter were safe, she dragged you out to the Compound to try her suspicions
  • and if meeting Carol gave you a jolt through your body, meeting Natasha was like seeing the world in a new light, a sense of ease and comfort washing over you once she caught your eye and smiled
  • (nat’s platonic soulmate is Tony because ironwidow is arguably one of the best friendships no one @ me)
